      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "Suggested updated to this answer.... I had to modify this solution to work for connecting to java on a windows machine with multiple network interfaces.  Only setting address=*:4000 allowed me to connect to the java process from my IDE on another computer.  My final working solution is &#39;-Xdebug Xrunjdwp:server=y,transport=dt_socket,address=*:4000,suspend&zwnj;&#8203;=n&#39;."
