    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Steps:</p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Start your remote java application with debugging options as said in above post.  </li>\n<li>Configure Eclipse for remote debugging by specifying host and port.  </li>\n<li>Start remote debugging in Eclipse and wait for connection to succeed.  </li>\n<li>Setup breakpoint and debug.  </li>\n<li>If you want to debug from start of application use suspend=y , this will keep remote application suspended until you connect from eclipse.</li>\n</ol>\n\n<p>See <a href=\"http://javarevisited.blogspot.com/2011/02/how-to-setup-remote-debugging-in.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Step by Step guide on Java remote debugging</a> for full details.</p>\n"
  }, {
