    "last_activity_date" : 1614759158,
    "last_edit_date" : 1614759158,
    "creation_date" : 1567952282,
    "answer_id" : 57842735,
    "question_id" : 975271,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I'd like to emphasize that <strong>order of arguments is important</strong>.</p>\n<p><code>java -agentlib:jdwp=transport=dt_socket,server=y,suspend=n,address=8000 -jar app.jar</code> command <strong>opens debugger port</strong>,</p>\n<p>but <code>java -jar app.jar -agentlib:jdwp=transport=dt_socket,server=y,suspend=n,address=8000</code> command <strong>doesn't</strong>. It will pass everything after <strong>app.jar</strong> as command-line arguments.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 3276952,
      "reputation" : 51,
      "user_id" : 2758679,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/dd281a07f31c739e963ba2821d6477e0?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "JCompagner",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2758679/jcompagner"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1624020924,
    "creation_date" : 1624020924,
    "answer_id" : 68035542,
    "question_id" : 975271,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>for everybody that has the problem that if you really do remote debugging from 1 machine to the other then using :</p>\n<p>-agentlib:jdwp=transport=dt_socket,server=y,address=8000,suspend=n</p>\n<p>is not enough because that binds now (at least on unix/osx machines) to localhost so you can only connect to it from localhost.</p>\n<p>If you try to remote debug this then you will get connection refused for this. From i think Java 9 on you need to do:</p>\n<p>-agentlib:jdwp=transport=dt_socket,server=y,address=*:8000,suspend=n</p>\n<p>or give an ip that it needs to bind on for hat *</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 5280092,
      "reputation" : 1,
      "user_id" : 4215755,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b0a003c105a4a60b1e7efb5cfb2d9286?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "kabanowster",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/4215755/kabanowster"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1698329880,
    "creation_date" : 1698329880,
    "answer_id" : 77367809,
    "question_id" : 975271,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Every solution here is describing the method to attach debugger after the application starts.\nIn the &quot;debugger listening&quot; setup you need to set server=n and suspend=n. If not the Gradle will throw permission denied error.</p>\n<p>build.gradle:</p>\n<pre><code>run {\n    jvmArgs = [&quot;-agentlib:jdwp=transport=dt_socket,server=n,suspend=n,address=5005&quot;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  } ],
